what is this book of short horror stories a man talks to a psychiatrist about the boogey man or sandman that had lived in his son's closet son begins crying during the night is scared to go to bed scared of the open closet man walks into son's room to find creature hovering over son's crib when light is turned on creature retreats to the closet the man's first child was killed by this creature but the death was deemed sids the man has a second son whom the father tries to protect man becomes obsessed with open closets man's wife doesn't believe him and they divorce man moves to protect son thinks he is safe but creature eventually follows dad is losing sleep trying to stay awake and protect son from creature finally sleep deprivation takes its toll and creature gets to second son father thinks he is safe from creature now seeks counciling at the end of the story it turnes out that this whole time the shrink was actually the boogey man in a mask this story scared me silly when i was younger that story is called the boogeyman and it's from the stephen king book of short stories called night shift here's a link with a synopsis of the story http en wikipedia org wiki the boogeyman happy reading to you The Amber Spyglass Bogeyman Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Trapped in the Closet The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Miss Saigon Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) Shaggy dog story Characters of The Sandman Knots Landing Spidey Super Stories The Time Machine Sudden infant death syndrome The Subtle Knife The Shining (film) The Silence of the Lambs Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Dead Like Me Little Girl Lost (The Twilight Zone) The Death Gate Cycle Otello The Inside Scenes from a Memory Vegeta The Catcher in the Rye Friends EastEnders The Sandman (DC Comics Modern Age) Sin City Ramsey Campbell Fight Club The Hobbit The Tracey Ullman Show shorts Phoebe Halliwell The Pilgrim's Progress Grandview